<subSubSection id="E9C66514075EFFC513BA0479FC7AAE74" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC513BA0479FE8DA9AE" blockId="38.[130,776,1651,2028]" box="[132,277,1651,1677]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC513BA0499FF7CA988" blockId="38.[130,776,1651,2028]" box="[132,228,1683,1709]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC513BA0499FF7CA988" box="[132,228,1683,1709]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Carapace</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC513BA04B8FD60A8CE" blockId="38.[130,776,1651,2028]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Sub-cylindrical carapace; spiny rostrum; fusiform intercalated plate; narrow post-orbital area; deep and wide cervical groove, strongly inclined dorsally, inflected at carapace mid-height, joined to dorsal margin and to antennal groove; deep and wide antennal groove; short, wide gastro-orbital groove, deep and oblique, originating as a median inflexion of cervical groove; postcervical and branchiocardiac grooves subparallel, slightly curved, very close; deep postcervical groove, not joined to dorsal margin and interrupted in hepatic region; deep branchiocardiac groove, strongly inclined, not joined to dorsal margin.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC5101302D2FC57AFD7" blockId="38.[813,975,216,242]" box="[813,975,216,242]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">
<heading id="FA2B81F3075EFFC5101302D2FC57AFD7" box="[813,975,216,242]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" reason="8">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5101302D2FC57AFD7" box="[813,975,216,242]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Ornamentation</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC5101302FDFC7AAE74" blockId="38.[813,1455,247,337]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Carapace covered by small tubercles preceded by crescentshaped depressions; cephalic region with an oblique orbital row of tubercles.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9C66514075EFFC51013037DFBC0AB0A" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC51013037DFC36AEAA" blockId="38.[811,1458,375,1071]" box="[813,942,375,401]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">DISCUSSION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC51013039DFC55AD95" blockId="38.[811,1458,375,1071]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">
Known by a single cast of carapace, this species was originally assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5108E03BDFB3EAEF4" authority="(Beurlen 1928)" baseAuthorityName="Beurlen" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[944,1190,438,465]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5108E03BDFC6DAEF5" box="[944,1013,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Eryma</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C54D4B6E075EFFC5173803BCFB03AEF4" author="BEURLEN K." box="[1030,1179,438,465]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" pagination="115 - 278" refId="ref29932" refString="BEURLEN K. 1928. - Die Decapoden des Schwabischen Jura mit Ausnahme der aus den oberjurassischen Plattenkalken stammenden. Palaeontographica 70: 115 - 278." type="journal article" year="1928">Beurlen 1928</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and then regarded as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5108D03DDFB1FAED5" baseAuthorityName="Schlotheim" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[947,1159,470,496]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modestiforme">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5108D03DDFB1FAED5" box="[947,1159,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Eryma modestiforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="C54D4B6E075EFFC5178003DDFAD0AED5" author="FORSTER R." box="[1214,1352,470,497]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" pagination="61 - 175" refId="ref32323" refString="FORSTER R. 1966. - Uber die Erymiden, eine alte konservative Familie der mesozoischen Dekapoden. Palaeontographica, Abt. A, 125 (4 - 6): 61 - 175." type="journal article" year="1966">Förster 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Careful examination of the 
<typeStatus id="7E67883D075EFFC5173503FCFBF4AD35" box="[1035,1132,502,528]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">holotype</typeStatus>
clearly shows the absence of junction between postcervical and branchiocardiac grooves and the interruption of the postcervical in the hepatic region. This groove pattern is diagnostic of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51783005CFACAAD55" authorityName="Beurlen" authorityYear="1928" box="[1213,1362,598,624]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51783005CFACAAD55" box="[1213,1362,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Stenodactylina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. So, the new combination 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC510CD007CFAB0ADB5" authorityName="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Beurlen" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[1011,1320,630,656]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoventrosa" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC510CD007CFAB0ADB5" box="[1011,1320,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Stenodactylina pseudoventrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="889B57F6075EFFC51609007CFA00ADB5" box="[1335,1432,630,656]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is here proposed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC5107D00BFFBC0AB0A" blockId="38.[811,1458,375,1071]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">
The strong proximity of the postcervical and branchiocardiac grooves allows the distinction of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC517B000DCFAD9ADCA" authorityName="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Beurlen" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[1166,1345,725,752]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoventrosa" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC517B000DCFAD9ADCA" box="[1166,1345,725,752]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. pseudoventrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="889B57F6075EFFC5167100DCFA28ADCA" box="[1359,1456,725,752]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5105700FCFB9EAC2A" baseAuthorityName="Cronier &amp; Courville" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[873,1030,757,784]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burgundiaca">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5105700FCFB9EAC2A" box="[873,1030,757,784]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. burgundiaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5170300FCFB4CAC2A" baseAuthorityName="Moret" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[1085,1236,757,784]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delphinensis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5170300FCFB4CAC2A" box="[1085,1236,757,784]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. delphinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, the ventral extremity of the postcervical groove of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC517CB011CFA30AC0A" authorityName="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Beurlen" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[1269,1448,789,816]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoventrosa" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC517CB011CFA30AC0A" box="[1269,1448,789,816]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. pseudoventrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="889B57F6075EFFC51013013CFC08AC6A" box="[813,912,821,848]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is lower than in 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5176C013FFB69AC6A" baseAuthorityName="Cronier &amp; Courville" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[1106,1265,821,847]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burgundiaca">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5176C013FFB69AC6A" box="[1106,1265,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. burgundiaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5163F013FFAC0AC6A" baseAuthorityName="Wright" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1281,1368,821,847]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guisei">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5163F013FFAC0AC6A" box="[1281,1368,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. guisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51656013FFC36AC4A" authority="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier, 2021" authorityName="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier" authorityYear="2021" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shotoverigiganti" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51656013FFC36AC4A" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. shotoverigiganti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="889B57F6075EFFC5108B015CFC69AC55" box="[949,1009,854,880]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC510C3015FFBF6AC4A" baseAuthorityName="Stenzel" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[1021,1134,853,879]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triglypta">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC510C3015FFBF6AC4A" box="[1021,1134,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. triglypta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51795015FFAB9AC4A" baseAuthorityName="Feldmann &amp; Haggart" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[1195,1313,853,879]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="walkerae">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51795015FFAB9AC4A" box="[1195,1313,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. walkerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Contrary to 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51013017FFC03ACAA" baseAuthorityName="Secretan" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[813,923,885,911]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51013017FFC03ACAA" box="[813,923,885,911]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51099017FFBDBACAA" baseAuthorityName="Cronier &amp; Courville" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[935,1091,885,911]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burgundiaca">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51099017FFBDBACAA" box="[935,1091,885,911]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. burgundiaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5176E017FFB7EACAA" baseAuthorityName="Moret" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[1104,1254,885,911]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delphinensis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5176E017FFB7EACAA" box="[1104,1254,885,911]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. delphinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC517CC017FFA31ACAA" baseAuthorityName="Van Straelen" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[1266,1449,885,911]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deslongchampsi">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC517CC017FFA31ACAA" box="[1266,1449,885,911]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. deslongchampsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51013019FFC2FAC8A" baseAuthorityName="Secretan" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[813,951,917,943]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulifera">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51013019FFC2FAC8A" box="[813,951,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. granulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC510FD019FFB8EAC8A" baseAuthorityName="Wright" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[963,1046,917,943]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guisei">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC510FD019FFB8EAC8A" box="[963,1046,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. guisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51770019FFB25AC8A" baseAuthorityName="Stenzel" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[1102,1213,917,943]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triglypta">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51770019FFB25AC8A" box="[1102,1213,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. triglypta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an orbital row is present in 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5104701BFFBB5ACEA" authorityName="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Beurlen" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[889,1069,949,975]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoventrosa">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5104701BFFBB5ACEA" box="[889,1069,949,975]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. pseudoventrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There are also depressions and no coarse elements in its ornamentation contrary to 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5160601DFFA30ACCB" baseAuthorityName="Secretan" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[1336,1448,980,1007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5160601DFFA30ACCB" box="[1336,1448,980,1007]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5101301FFFC75AB2B" baseAuthorityName="Van Straelen" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[813,1005,1012,1039]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deslongchampsi">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5101301FFFC75AB2B" box="[813,1005,1012,1039]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. deslongchampsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC510C301FFFB13AB2B" baseAuthorityName="Hyzny, Schlogl, Charbonnier, Schweigert, Rulleau &amp; Gouttenoire" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[1021,1163,1012,1039]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lagardettei">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC510C301FFFB13AB2B" box="[1021,1163,1012,1039]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. lagardettei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC517A501FFFAF8AB2B" authority="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier, 2021" authorityName="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier" authorityYear="2021" box="[1179,1376,1012,1039]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shotoverigiganti" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC517A501FFFAF8AB2B" box="[1179,1376,1012,1039]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. shotoverigiganti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="889B57F6075EFFC5165401FFFA32AB2A" box="[1386,1450,1013,1039]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51011061FFC06AB0B" baseAuthorityName="Stenzel" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[815,926,1044,1071]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triglypta">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51011061FFC06AB0B" box="[815,926,1044,1071]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. triglypta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC510E5061FFBC9AB0B" baseAuthorityName="Feldmann &amp; Haggart" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[987,1105,1044,1071]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="walkerae">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC510E5061FFBC9AB0B" box="[987,1105,1044,1071]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. walkerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
